{"id": "EUVD-2025-13134", "enisaUuid": "a1d5d550-51f3-3889-86af-ff5a935f1983", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnet/smc: fix NULL sndbuf_desc in smc_cdc_tx_handler()\n\nWhen performing a stress test on SMC-R by rmmod mlx5_ib driver\nduring the wrk/nginx test, we found that there is a probability\nof triggering a panic while terminating all link groups.\n\nThis issue dues to the race between smc_smcr_terminate_all()\nand smc_buf_create().\n\n\t\t\tsmc_smcr_terminate_all\n\nsmc_buf_create\n/* init */\nconn->sndbuf_desc = NULL;\n...\n\n\t\t\t__smc_lgr_terminate\n\t\t\t\tsmc_conn_kill\n\t\t\t\t\tsmc_close_abort\n\t\t\t\t\t\tsmc_cdc_get_slot_and_msg_send\n\n\t\t\t__softirqentry_text_start\n\t\t\t\tsmc_wr_tx_process_cqe\n\t\t\t\t\tsmc_cdc_tx_handler\n\t\t\t\t\t\tREAD(conn->sndbuf_desc->len);\n\t\t\t\t\t\t/* panic dues to NULL sndbuf_desc */\n\nconn->sndbuf_desc = xxx;\n\nThis patch tries to fix the issue by always to check the sndbuf_desc\nbefore send any cdc msg, to make sure that no null pointer is\nseen during cqe processing.", "datePublished": "2025-05-02T18:31:36", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-10T18:30:29", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-53110", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/22a825c541d775c1dbe7b2402786025acad6727b", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/31817c530768b0199771ec6019571b4f0ddbf230", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/3c270435db8aa34929263dddae8fd050f5216ecb", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/3ebac7cf0a184a8102821a7a00203f02bebda83c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b108bd9e6be000492ebebe867daa699285978a10"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-53110", "GHSA-vm5r-r7q6-4cwx"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0c3c83b8-a57d-3118-b4c0-1b4ff53bd2ae", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "0b29ec6436138721acf5844e558f7334a0fa61d5 <22a825c541d775c1dbe7b2402786025acad6727b"}, {"id": "31b68fe8-6167-31d1-bc41-04750a309836", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "3d62864b-2a01-367d-be53-ac8d8be2a574", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.104"}, {"id": "5500ba54-4931-3033-be05-49fd5ae8d425", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "0b29ec6436138721acf5844e558f7334a0fa61d5 <b108bd9e6be000492ebebe867daa699285978a10"}, {"id": "6d4c7a9d-1da6-3777-a761-54e502b7dc1d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.2.8"}, {"id": "70a8b33d-7c0f-3c1d-aebb-9cf152677ce3", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.3"}, {"id": "7382c00f-7980-3d13-8007-5ae9284ead97", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.21"}, {"id": "a06660dc-3306-3500-9703-7ca24fa6ae84", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.10.176"}, {"id": "accd35e0-b663-3000-b97a-83c1e4c75e71", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "0b29ec6436138721acf5844e558f7334a0fa61d5 <31817c530768b0199771ec6019571b4f0ddbf230"}, {"id": "bc97c63b-5fcc-3632-92cc-116ad944c670", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "0b29ec6436138721acf5844e558f7334a0fa61d5 <3c270435db8aa34929263dddae8fd050f5216ecb"}, {"id": "c2fbd630-956d-32f4-8f03-46839375fe02", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.5"}, {"id": "f15a3bc4-ad8c-35e1-bd54-9eaf01a9dbcd", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "0b29ec6436138721acf5844e558f7334a0fa61d5 <3ebac7cf0a184a8102821a7a00203f02bebda83c"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "215081a9-db0c-3862-8cb1-4a621ebb341c", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}